<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

    <main class="py-8 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                    <div class="bg-white">
                        <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                            <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                            <span class="mx-2">></span>
                            <a href="/gardening" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Gardening</a>
                            <span class="mx-2">></span>
                            <span class="text-gray-800">Gardening Mistakes</span>
                        </nav>

                        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                            Gardening Mistakes to Avoid for a Healthy Garden
                        </h1>

                        <div class="mb-8">
                            <img src="/images/gardening-mistakes.webp" alt="Healthy garden tips"
                                class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                        </div>

                        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                Gardening can be relaxing, rewarding, and a great way to improve your home’s outdoor
                                space. But even small errors can lead to weak plants, poor growth, and wasted time and
                                money. Many people start gardening with excitement, but they don’t realize how sensitive
                                plants can be to the wrong conditions.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                The good news is that most Gardening Mistakes are easy to fix once you understand what
                                causes them. This guide will help you avoid the most common problems, grow healthier
                                plants, and enjoy better results in every season.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Why Gardening Mistakes Happen So Often</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Most gardening problems happen because beginners follow random tips without
                                understanding their plants. Every plant needs the right balance of sunlight, water,
                                soil, and care. When one factor is missing, growth becomes slow or unhealthy.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Another reason is impatience. Many gardeners expect quick results and overdo things like
                                watering, fertilizing, or pruning. Gardening works best with consistent care and a
                                simple routine instead of rushing the process.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Gardening Mistakes Related to Watering</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Watering seems simple, but it is one of the biggest causes of plant failure. Too much
                                water can rot the roots, and too little water can dry out the plant quickly.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Overwatering Your Plants</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Overwatering is one of the most common Gardening Mistakes. When soil stays wet all the
                                time, plant roots do not get enough oxygen. This can lead to root rot, fungus, and weak
                                plant growth.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                A simple way to avoid this problem is to check the soil before watering. If the top
                                layer is still moist, wait another day. Most plants grow better with deep watering less
                                often rather than light watering every day.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Underwatering in Hot Weather</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Underwatering is also a big issue, especially during summer. Plants lose water quickly
                                due to heat and wind. If your plant looks dull, drooping, or dry, it may need more
                                frequent watering.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                The best time to water is early morning. This helps water reach the roots before the sun
                                gets too strong. Watering at night can sometimes increase moisture-related diseases,
                                especially in humid areas.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Gardening Mistakes Related to Soil</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Soil is the foundation of every garden. Even if you buy good plants, they will not grow
                                well in poor soil.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Using the Wrong Soil Type</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Different plants need different soil conditions. Some plants like loose, sandy soil,
                                while others prefer rich and slightly moist soil. If the soil is too hard or drains
                                poorly, roots cannot spread properly.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                A basic soil test can help you understand your soil type. You can also improve soil
                                quality by adding compost, coco peat, or organic matter to support plant growth.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Forgetting to Add Compost or Nutrients</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Plants need nutrients to grow strong leaves, flowers, and fruits. If the soil lacks
                                nutrients, plants become weak and produce fewer flowers or vegetables.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Adding compost is one of the easiest ways to feed your garden naturally. It improves
                                soil structure and supports healthy roots. This is an important step to avoid long-term
                                Gardening Mistakes that reduce plant growth.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Gardening Mistakes Related to Sunlight</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Sunlight is just as important as water. Many plants need the correct amount of sun to
                                grow properly, but people often place them in the wrong location.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Placing Plants in the Wrong Light Conditions</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Some plants need full sunlight, while others grow best in partial shade. If a sun-loving
                                plant is placed in shade, it grows slowly and looks weak. If a shade plant is placed in
                                direct sun, its leaves may burn and dry out.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Always read plant labels or search the sunlight requirement before planting. This small
                                step prevents many common gardening failures.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Ignoring Seasonal Sun Changes</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                The sun’s direction changes during different seasons. A location that gets good sun in
                                winter may become too hot in summer. That’s why it’s important to observe your garden
                                space during the year.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                If possible, use pots for sensitive plants so you can move them when needed. This helps
                                protect plants and reduces Gardening Mistakes related to heat stress.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Gardening Mistakes While Planting</h2>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Planting Too Close Together</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                When plants are too close, they compete for sunlight, water, and nutrients. Crowded
                                plants also reduce airflow, which increases pest problems and fungal diseases.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Always follow spacing guidelines. Giving plants room helps them grow bigger, healthier,
                                and stronger. Proper spacing also makes your garden look cleaner and easier to maintain.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Planting at the Wrong Time</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Some plants grow best in cool weather, while others need warm temperatures. Planting at
                                the wrong time can lead to poor germination and slow growth.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                If you want better success, choose plants according to your local climate and season.
                                This is one of the most important ways to avoid Gardening Mistakes early in the process.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Gardening Mistakes with Fertilizers and Chemicals</h2>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Over-Fertilizing Your Garden</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Too much fertilizer can burn roots and leaves. It can also cause fast leaf growth with
                                fewer flowers or fruits. Many gardeners think more fertilizer means better growth, but
                                it often creates the opposite result.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Use fertilizer only when needed and follow the instructions on the product. Organic
                                options like compost and natural manure are safer for long-term gardening.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Using Harsh Chemicals Without Need</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Using chemicals too often can kill beneficial insects and reduce soil quality. It can
                                also make plants dependent on chemicals instead of building natural strength.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                If pests appear, first try gentle solutions like neem spray, soap water, or manual
                                removal. These methods are safer and help you avoid major Gardening Mistakes that harm
                                the environment.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Gardening Mistakes Related to Maintenance</h2>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Not Removing Weeds Early</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Weeds compete with plants for nutrients and water. They also attract pests and make the
                                garden look messy. If you remove weeds early, it becomes much easier to control them.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Mulching is a great way to reduce weeds. It also keeps the soil moist and improves the
                                overall look of your garden.
                            </p>

                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Skipping Pruning and Deadheading</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Pruning helps plants grow in a healthy shape. Deadheading means removing old flowers so
                                the plant can produce new blooms.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                If you never prune or remove dead parts, plants may become weak and stop flowering
                                properly. Regular care prevents many Gardening Mistakes and keeps your garden fresh.
                            </p>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">FAQs</h2>
                            <div class="space-y-6">
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">What are the most common Gardening Mistakes beginners make?</h3>
                                    <p class="text-gray-700">Beginners often overwater, use poor soil, plant in the wrong sunlight, and overcrowd plants. These mistakes can be fixed with simple care and planning.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">How often should I water my garden?</h3>
                                    <p class="text-gray-700">It depends on weather, plant type, and soil. Most gardens do well with deep watering a few times a week instead of daily light watering.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Is compost necessary for gardening?</h3>
                                    <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, compost improves soil quality and adds nutrients. It helps plants grow stronger and reduces the need for chemical fertilizers.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Can I garden successfully in small spaces?</h3>
                                    <p class="text-gray-700">Yes. You can use pots, vertical gardening, and small raised beds. With good sunlight and watering, small gardens can be very productive.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">How can I prevent Gardening Mistakes in the future?</h3>
                                    <p class="text-gray-700">Follow a simple routine, observe your plants regularly, and learn what each plant needs. Small daily attention prevents big problems.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                Gardening becomes much easier when you avoid the most common Gardening Mistakes. Simple
                                changes like watering correctly, improving soil, providing the right sunlight, and
                                planting with proper spacing can greatly improve your results.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">
                                Start with small steps and focus on consistency. Over time, you will learn what works
                                best for your plants, and your garden will grow healthier, greener, and more beautiful
                                every season.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </article>

